comments.comment:
		Actually, it's TBB memory leak. You can create valgrind suppression file (see <denchmark-link:http://valgrind.org/docs/manual/manual-core.html#manual-core.suppress>http://valgrind.org/docs/manual/manual-core.html#manual-core.suppress</denchmark-link>
) with the following content:
<denchmark-code>{
   TBB - allocate_via_handler_v3 issue
   Memcheck:Leak
   fun:malloc
   fun:_ZN3tbb8internal23allocate_via_handler_v3Em
}
</denchmark-code>

And send the merge-request with it to OpenCV. So, any other users can use this file and add new suppressions. It can be very useful to distinct OpenCV memory leaks from 3rdparty ones.
